$interpreted: Baa Baa: Moya!? You want to go to Moya!?
Tindoiimu: That's right.
Baa Baa: You can't go there!
Baa Baa: You'll die! Jump down there and you're not coming back!
Baa Baa: It's a death pit!
Tindoiimu: I know, I understand... But Jiyanama raised me. I can't abandon her.
Baa Baa: ...Hmph, if you're set on it then... I guess it's not completely impossible.
Baa Baa: My dad was part of the demihuman trade union back in the day, and he used a secret path... it cut right through Moya.
Tindoiimu: Really!?
Baa Baa: Yeah. It saved heaps of time with transport, so they risked it. It was the union's own secret. Dad only brought me through it once.
Tindoiimu: Do you remember where it is? Can you bring me?
Baa Baa: I have an idea... but that was back before Moya was filled with nian.
Baa Baa: Nian—they're ruthless beasts. They eat people. Even if we could get inside, I don't know how safe it is anymore.
Tindoiimu: I'll deal with the nian. Just help me, I'll pay anything you want!
Baa Baa: You're not going to take no for an answer, eh?
Tindoiimu: No. I won't.
Baa Baa: Alright, I can take you.
Baa Baa: But I've got my dad's debt to repay. I'll need to get something else out of it...
Baa Baa: Nian pelts go for a pretty penny. So if you're really keen on dealing with them, I won't say no.
Tindoiimu: Don't worry about it. Like I said—you guide, I'll deal with the beasts.
Baa Baa: Then it's a deal.
Jiyanama: Don't come any closer!
Tindoiimu: That's Jiyanama's voice!
Baa Baa: Came from over there!
Jiyanama: Help me!
Baa Baa: Choice, mate! Pelts pelts pelts!
Jiyanama: Princess, you... why are you here!?
Jiyanama: Once you're in Moya you can't leave... I can't forgive myself for getting you into this. I'm so sorry...
Tindoiimu: I'm not the only one you should apologize to.
Tindoiimu: Doing what you did... you've given the Alliance all the leverage they need!
Tindoiimu: You've put the tribe in incredible danger just so you could avenge Faayida, so you can have your justice!
Jiyanama: I know, princess. I know that regardless of what I do, Faayida will never return.
Tindoiimu: ......
Jiyanama: But If I don't keep fighting, then it won't only be Faayida I've lost...
Jiyanama: It'll be my responsibility as a mother. That's all I have left...
Jiyanama: Princess, this is... something you can't understand...
Baa Baa: Alright, I think I'm all pelted up!
Baa Baa: So whaddaya say we blow this popsicle stand?
Baa Baa: Found it~ Ol' Baa Baa's still got it!

Baa Baa: *Ahem*
"The earth we stand, mountain protector.
From wind and thunder, water and fire."
Baa Baa: "We face the wind, with fires behind, and earth below, the looming skies."
Baa Baa: I think this should be correct...
Jiyanama: Oh my, it's another road!
Baa Baa: You have to follow me closely now. Don't wander off. One false step and you could get lost, and I won't be able to save you.
Tindoiimu: Understood... Lead the way.
